The paper deals with image enhancement and denoising, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) categories. The proposed method involves the use of weight matrices to suppress noise, which is related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also mentions enforcing spatial smoothness, which is a common technique in graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the paper uses a Retinex model, which is a popular method in machine learning (cs.LG).
